      • addDefaultPrefixModule

        public BreadBotClientBuilder addDefaultPrefixModule(java.lang.String prefix)
        This module provides a static prefix that cannot be changed. By default, the prefix is set to "!".

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultPrefixModule(prefix))

        You can define a different prefix implementation by providing a class to addModule(ICommandModule...) that implements IPrefixModule

      • addDefaultAdminModule

        public BreadBotClientBuilder addDefaultAdminModule()
        This enables the @Admin annotation that is marked on Command classes. This ensures that Commands marked with @Admin are only usable by Administrators.

        It is important to include an implementation of IAdminModule through either this method, addAdminModule(Predicate), or your own implementation. Otherwise, all users will have access to Administrative Commands

        The default criteria for defining an Administrator is as follows:

        • Has Kick Members Permission
        • Is higher than the bot on the role hierarchy

        Different criteria to determine which member has administrative status with addAdminModule(Predicate) or your own implementation of IAdminModule

      • addAdminModule

        public BreadBotClientBuilder addAdminModule(java.util.function.Predicate<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Member> isAdmin)
        Define custom behavior to determine which members can use Commands marked with @Admin

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultAdminModule(isAdmin))

      • build

        public BreadBotClient build(net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.IEventManager eventManager)
        Builds the BreadBotClient with the provided EventManager. It is at this point that all Modules are initialized and Commands built. If an IPrefixModule has not been provided, a new DefaultPrefixModule("!") is provided.
        Parameters:
        eventManager - The IEventManager of which to attach all the listeners (CommandModules) to. If the module is an instanceof InterfacedEventManager it will only use IEventManager.register(Object) on Modules that extend EventListener. Otherwise, the BreadBotClient will register all the CommandModules as listeners.
        Returns:
        a new BreadBotClient.
